{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 400°F. Line the base of a springform pan with parchment, grease sides of pan and set aside.","Place flour, butter, cream cheese, baking powder and 1 tsp salt into mixing bowl and knead <strong><b>3 min\/<b><\/strong>. Transfer dough to a floured surface and form into a ball.","Roll dough out between 2 sheets of cling wrap to a circle (approx. 14 in.) with a rolling pin. Line prepared pan with rolled dough and gently push into base and around edges up to 2 inches high. Prick base with a fork to avoid air bubbles and pre-bake for 10 minutes (400°F). Meanwhile, place cheese into mixing bowl and grate <strong><b>10 sec\/speed 5<b><\/strong>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place green leeks into mixing bowl and chop <b>10 sec\/speed 5<b>.","Add chopped white leeks and water and cook <b>12 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Drain leeks through simmering basket, place leeks into pre-baked crust and discard water.","Reduce oven temperature to 350°F.","Place reserved grated cheese, cream, eggs, ham, pepper, ½ tsp salt and nutmeg into mixing bowl and mix <strong><b>15 sec\/\/speed 4<b><\/strong>. Pour over the leeks,  stir through with spatula and bake for 45 minutes (350°F). Cut into pieces and serve hot."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["7 oz all-purpose flour","3 ½ oz unsalted butter, chilled, cut into pieces, plus extra to grease","3 ½ oz cream cheese","1 tsp baking powder","1 ½ tsp salt, divided","7 oz Gouda, cut into ¾ in. pieces","8 ½ oz leeks, green part, cut into 1 in. pieces (see Tip)","5 ½ oz leeks, white part, cut into ⅛ in. rounds","14 oz water","7 oz heavy whipping cream","4 large eggs","5 ½ oz ham, diced","¼ tsp ground black pepper","1 pinch ground nutmeg"]}],"id":"r174137","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-Vox-ZXlQZiI\/XZWeMZ7Fn_I\/AAAAAAAAewU\/WhLFBabfg5suIIK41xOdC7AKnn3GTQRpQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_V1LNJE6juKCMdQr2.png","title":"Leek Pie","publishedAt":"2017-05-26T00:00:00Z","nu